The paper deals with the application of lattice theory to rough sets and matroids, which are both topics in discrete mathematics. Therefore, cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of linear algebra and graph theory, which are topics in cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper discusses data pre-processing in data mining, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
